This software is in EXPERIMENTAL state and not for production use. It's currently just a proof of concept.

This application is written in PHP and intended to create Doctrine1 and Doctrine2 schema files
from MySQL Workbench Files (*.mwb). It is inspired by http://code.google.com/p/mysql-workbench-doctrine-plugin/.

To create models use it as follows. (do not forget to implement a class autoloading mechanism like in
the example)

<?php

// enable autoloading of classes
require_once('lib/MwbExporter/Core/SplClassLoader.php');
$classLoader = new SplClassLoader();
$classLoader->setIncludePath('lib');
$classLoader->register();

// define a formatter
$formatter = new \MwbExporter\Formatter\Doctrine2\Annotation\Loader();

// parse the mwb file
$mwb = new \MwbExporter\Core\Workbench\Document('myDatabaseModel.mwb', $formatter);

// show the output
echo $mwb->display();
?>

Support for behaviours is implemented for Doctrine1. Use the comment fields in tables.
{d:actAs}
  actAs:
    timestampable:
      [..]
{/d:actAs}